ORDER OF THE PRESIDENT OF THE
INTER-AMERICAN COURT OF HUMAN RIGHTS
OF SEPTEMBER 25, 1997
PROVISIONAL MEASURES
LVAREZ ET AL. CASE
HAVING SEEN:
1. The order of the Inter-American Court of Human Rights of September 19,
1997, in which it decided
to convene the Inter-American Commission on Human Rights and the State of Colombia
to a public hearing to be held at the seat of the Court on November 4, 1997, at 10.00
a.m., to hear their arguments on the provisional measures requested in the [.] [lvarez
et al.] case.
CONSIDERING:
That, having reviewed the agenda of work for the XXXVIII Regular Session of
the Inter-American Court of Human Rights, the President considered it necessary to
restructure this in order to accomplish the planned objectives and therefore the date
of the public hearing established by this Court in its order of September 19, 1997,
must be modified.
THEREFORE:
THE PRESIDENT OF THE INTER-AMERICAN COURT
OF HUMAN RIGHTS,
pursuant to Article 12.2 of the Statute of the Inter-American Court of Human Rights
and Article 4 of the Rules of Procedure of the Inter-American Court of Human Rights,
DECIDES:
To convene the Inter-American Commission on Human Rights and the State
of Colombia to a public hearing to be held at the seat of the Inter-American Court of
Human Rights on November 8, 1997, at 10.00 a.m., in order to hear their arguments
on the provisional measures requested in the instant case, and a hearing prior to this
at 9.00 a.m. on the same day.
Hernn Salgado-Pesantes
President
Manuel E. Ventura-Robles
Secretary
2
So ordered,
Hernn Salgado-Pesantes
President
Manuel E. Ventura-Robles
Secretary
